If we can’t guarantee that at a grass venue maybe it makes sense to play it somewhere we can get that.’ 

GB captain Leon Smith, a Glaswegian himself, said there was ‘no chance’ of finding or creating a suitably large outdoor venue – a minimum of 600 seats are required – in order to bring a grass-court tie to Scotland.

But he added: ‘I say no chance but I’m not a lawn expert. So, if someone can tell me there’s a chance, I’m sure we would explore it. 

